name: r-pool
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.1.6" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-pool
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/pool_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/pool/pool_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: cdbe5f6c7f757c01893dc9870df0fb8d300829da0e427f6c2559b01caa52d9e1

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dbi
    - r-r6
    - r-dbplyr
    - r-dplyr
    - r-later
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dbi
    - r-r6
    - r-dbplyr
    - r-dplyr
    - r-later

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('pool')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('pool')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/rstudio/pool
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: Enables the creation of object pools, which make it less computationally expensive to fetch a new object. Currently the only supported pooled objects are 'DBI' connections.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - halldc

# Type: Package
# Title: Object Pooling
# Version: 0.1.4.2
